results.name: Number of primes which use each of 0-to-n decimal digits exactly once.
comment: There are exactly 16 five-digit primes using decimal digits 0-to-4 exactly once: A109176 and 2668 eight-digit primes using each of 0-to-7 decimal digits exactly once: A109177, A109178. Cf. A094258.
results.author: _Zak Seidov_, Jun 21 2005
